de.mrapp.android.adapter.decorator

Class AbstractExpandableListDecorator<GroupType,ChildType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mrapp.android.adapter.decorator.AbstractDecorator
      • de.mrapp.android.adapter.decorator.AbstractExpandableListDecorator<GroupType,ChildType>
  • Type Parameters:
    GroupType - The type of the underlying data of the adapter's group items
    ChildType - The type of the underlying data of the adapter's child items
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExpandableListDecorator, SelectableExpandableListDecorator

    public abstract class AbstractExpandableListDecorator<GroupType,ChildType>
extends AbstractDecorator
    An abstract base class for all decorators, which should allow to customize the appearance of the view, which is used to visualize the items of a ExpandableListAdapter, SingleChoiceExpandableListAdapter or MultipleChoiceExpandableListAdapter.
    Since:
    0.2.0

    • Method Detail

      • getGroupType

        public int getGroupType(GroupType group)
        The method which is invoked in order to retrieve the view type of a specific group item, which is about to be visualized. This method has to be overridden by custom decorators which should be able to visualize some group items optically divergent from others, returning a different integer constant for each type.
        Parameters:
        group - The group item, which should be visualized, as an instance of the generic type GroupType. The group item may not be null
        Returns:
        The view type of the group item, which is about to be visualized, as an Integer value

      • getGroupTypeCount

        public int getGroupTypeCount()
        Returns the number of view types, which are used by the decorator in order to visualize child items. This method has to be overridden by custom decorators in order to return a value, which is consistent with the implementation of the getChildViewType-method.
        Returns:
        The number of view types, which are used by the decorator in order to visualize child items, as an Integer value

      • inflateGroupView

        public final View inflateGroupView(LayoutInflater inflater,
                                   ViewGroup parent,
                                   GroupType group)
        The method which is invoked by an adapter to inflate the view, which should be used to visualize a specific group item.
        Parameters:
        inflater - The inflater, which should be used to inflate the view, as an instance of the class LayoutInflater. The inflater may not be null
        parent - The parent view of the view, which should be inflated, as an instance of the class ViewGroup or null, if no parent view is available
        group - The group item, which should be visualized, as an instance of the generic type GroupType. The item may not be null
        Returns:
        The view, which has been inflated, as an instance of the class View. The view may not be null
